##On the first day back to work, the examination of epidemic prevention in Beijing office buildings

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

Greater control over Golden Place and office buildings on Tai Mong Road.

REPORTER: Sun Meixin

Shortage of materials and manpower is a difficult problem faced by the epidemic prevention of office buildings.

Shortage of materials and manpower is a difficult problem faced by the epidemic prevention of office buildings.

”

Although a few days ago the company's personnel department has sent several e-mails encouraging employees to return to work at home, but the first day of official resumption of work, Luyuan still chose to go to the company to get some information: "also look at the company's management and control. "

Wearing a mask, goggles and gloves, Luyuan, fully armed, decided to drive herself to the office. Unlike the usual company parking lots, which are hard to find, the first day back was empty.

Lu Yuan went through a smooth process of taking body temperature, filling in registration forms and checking masks. "there was no need for toothpicks in the elevator, but they were fitted with Kleenex. " Except for a few people, everyone was wearing masks, lu Yuan didn't think it made much difference.

Still, she was afraid to stick around the office long enough to finish her work and leave quickly. In addition to concerns about air conditioning, a possible transmission channel, Lu said that the maximum length of stay at the company was set at four hours.

"compared with the Spring Festival holiday, the number of people in the buildings under management has increased significantly on the first day of the resumption of work, " said Zhou Yehui, head of the real estate management department in the north China district of the Cbre Group, which is based on the statistics of temperature measurements taken by building staff when entering the buildings. "But compared with the number of people who have returned to the office buildings since the Spring Festival in previous years, the proportion of people returning to the office buildings is only 20-25 percent of that in normal times. Most companies are choosing to work from home this week."

The proportion of enterprises returning to work in Super Grade A office buildings in the core area of Beijing is relatively low. "In the case of the projects we manage in the financial street, the resumption rate is about 30 per cent, " Zhou observed, noting that more small and medium enterprises were being restored in non-core areas such as Jiuxianqiao and North Tetraloop.

Liu Xiaowei, the property manager of the Jindi Center on Beijing's Dawang Road, said that on the first day of resuming work, the number of people going in and out of the office building is much smaller than in the previous survey: "when the survey was conducted, 50 companies said they wanted to resume work, and it was expected that 1,000 people would go in and out. But only 400 people actually entered the building on the first day, less than 10 per cent of the total number of employees, and only 35, or 40 per cent of the total number of companies that have returned to work."

In order to reduce the gathering of personnel as much as possible, before resuming work, the golden center mobilizes the enterprises to go to and from work. "There are temperature measuring points at the entrances and exits of offices and shopping malls, and everyone should keep a distance of more than one meter, " Liu said, adding that there are strict limits on the number of people who can take the elevators, each car can only take a maximum of 6 people: "But the actual operation, most of the people into the building is also very aware of precautions, the elevator station 2,3 people choose to wait for the next. "

Because it is located in the subway transfer and commercial core area, and in order to avoid the blind spot of control, Jindi Square, in conjunction with the Beijing subway department, closed the entrance and exit of the shopping mall connecting to the subway. Only three entrances were retained for the entire office building and commercial section, it's easier to control.

Jinmao property in the Sinochem building, Kaichen Shimao Center at the entrance of a variety of signs, including "designated drop mask" , "clean" , "ask registration" and so on, before entering the building warning.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Jin Mao property staff in front of the Office Mat for killing.

Temperature measurement, check wearing mask, enter the building registration, for the office has resumed work in the enterprise, this is the most basic property prevention and control process. In addition, many property units in the lobby or import and export have provided hand sanitizer, or alcohol disinfection. The floor mats in front of the doors are regularly disinfected with 84 disinfectants to reduce the possibility of external pathogens entering the building."

For Responsible Properties, the CBRE Group requires elevator boxes, buttons and public office areas to be disinfected once every two hours, and thoroughly disinfect details such as drains and floor drains, Chow said.

In response to the potential "threat" of air conditioning, properties have been converted to fresh air systems and are regularly eliminated.

Gold Center in the property to kill at the same time, require enterprises in their respective air intakes, regular spraying disinfection water. In addition to the regular elimination of the air conditioning, the positive pressure fresh air system is used to pressurize and pre-treat the outdoor air and send it into the room to avoid the circulation of the indoor air.

On the issue of food, the property is also as strictly guarded as possible.

Hongyang real estate is located in the office building of its Shanghai headquarters. The staff eating at the wrong peak occupy a table to eat alone, and keep a distance of about 2 meters. A staff sigh, the lunch out of the solemn sense of the examination room.

Different from the closed office building canteen, the Food and beverage area of Jindi Square "Big Food Generation" to bear the shopping mall and office staff two parts of the catering needs. "This part of the dining area is still open, but the tables and chairs have been rearranged. One table is only equipped with one chair, and there is only diagonal space between the tables to ensure that diners will eat at intervals, " Liu said, referring to office tenants, companies are also being mobilised to encourage staff to bring their own meals.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There are temperature measuring points and registers at the entrance and exit of Golden Square and Golden Center.

Chow said that for the canteen buildings, restaurants using food delivery system, by the property to each employee to the workplace, to avoid the possibility of cross-infection.

Because of Beijing's experience in fighting SARS 17 years ago, Zhou and his colleagues began to make preparations before the Spring Festival after the news of the pneumonia epidemic, one is the mobilization of Personnel: "There are a large number of outsourced personnel in the properties, so before the Spring Festival, we will mobilize with the outsourced companies, hoping that some housekeeping, security and other logistics personnel will not leave Beijing during the Spring Festival. " Therefore, at present, all the personnel working in the properties, neither left Beijing during the Spring Festival: "The risk of imported infections was avoided, and the quarantine time for return to Beijing was also avoided. "

Jinmao property requires property staff to carry out temperature testing twice a day, and to provide centralized management of accommodation staff, strict control of access to avoid epidemic among property staff.

However, with the "cloud office" time gradually over, the return of personnel office buildings, materials and staff ratio, property management is the focus of concern.

Zhou said that although a batch of protective materials, including protective clothing, masks and goggles, had been snapped up before the Spring Festival, it would last only a month because of the huge consumption. Although the follow-up materials are also ordered, but all industries are facing shortages of materials, whether can keep up with it is still a problem.

In addition, although early mobilization has left behind a number of property staff, the current staffing ratio is only 70 per cent of the normal level compared with the normal operating period, and the basic guaranteed number of staff to maintain building operation is currently used in each building.

"But as the number of people returning to the office building increases, there will be a lot of pressure on this group of people. If people leaving Beijing are still facing the problems of sealing off villages, sealing off cities and quarantining the return journey, the shortage of manpower will be a big problem,"Zhou said.

Jin and property agents in Suwannaphum expressed similar concerns. Liu Xiaowei said that according to the survey of customers, the official resumption of work is expected to be 17,23, and March several nodes, as more and more personnel into the building, worry about the pressure of management and control will increase.

The person in charge of Jinmao property also said that because many property employees are on duty during the Spring Festival, plus the intensity of work after resuming work, front-line employees will also have excessive fatigue, decreased immunity.

And for the office industry, the current most concerned about the problem, is rework may appear after the suspected and confirmed cases.

Ge Haifeng, vice president of China Holding and General Manager of China Index Data Division, said at an earlier business analysis meeting that if there is an outbreak in the building, no matter whether the business or the owner, will face a huge impact: "once the outbreak will be closed, then the building of other tenants have the right to request rent-free? "? What about the disruptions and obstructions that result from other tenants'operations? This raises a number of legal issues,"he said, even as companies resume work, epidemic prevention remains a top priority.
